# Headroom token compression (always on)

**Prerequisite:** `pip install "headroom-ai[all]"` — install once, then Cursor picks up the MCP server from `.cursor/mcp.json`.

## Always compress before reading into context

Before attaching any of the following to a prompt, call `headroom_compress`:

| Content type | Trigger |
|--------------|---------|
| File > 200 lines | any `read_file` / `cat` result |
| Build / test output | `npm run`, `npx tsc`, `gradlew`, `pytest`, CI logs |
| JSON tool output | API responses, `adb logcat`, `package-lock.json` |
| Search results | `grep`, `rg`, `gh issue list`, `gh run list` |
| Git diffs / logs | `git diff`, `git log --stat` with many files |
| Android logcat | any `adb logcat` dump |

## MCP tools

| Tool | When to call |
|------|-------------|
| `headroom_compress` | Before inserting large content into context |
| `headroom_retrieve` | When you need the full original of a compressed chunk |
| `headroom_stats` | To check session token savings |

## RTK — frugal shell commands

For every shell command that produces verbose output, prefix with `rtk`:

```bash
# Git (59-80% savings)
rtk git status          rtk git diff            rtk git log

# Build & lint (80-90% savings — errors only)
rtk npm run <script>    rtk tsc                 rtk lint

# Test (90-99% savings — failures only)
rtk npm test            rtk npx jest            rtk cargo test

# Files & search (60-75% savings)
rtk ls <path>           rtk read <file>         rtk grep <pattern>

# Android (85-90% savings)
rtk adb logcat          rtk docker logs <c>

# GitHub (26-87% savings)
rtk gh pr view <n>      rtk gh run list         rtk gh issue list
```

If `rtk` is not installed (`pip install "headroom-ai[all]"` includes it), fall back to raw commands.

## Rules

1. **Never** paste raw `adb logcat`, full `npm install`, or large JSON blobs into the chat uncompressed.
2. In command chains, prefix each segment: `rtk git add . && rtk git commit -m "msg"`.
3. Use `headroom_stats` at the end of a long session to report savings.
4. Compression is reversible — call `headroom_retrieve` with the hash if full content is needed.

## Setup reminder (one-time, already committed)

`.cursor/mcp.json` registers `headroom mcp serve` as a background MCP process.
Cursor starts it automatically — no manual steps needed after `pip install "headroom-ai[all]"`.
